<div id='contact-6556'><span class='name'>Robert Martin</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/6556/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
One of my favorite runs in the Obed System. I wouldn't do it lower than 3.4' and if you do it that<br/>
low you will be doing some knuckle walking, but still worth it if you've never done it before.<br/>
4.0-4.3 is a good level for the intermediate first timer. The river at the put-in bridge gauge is<br/>
very narrow and a few inches on the gauge don't make much difference at Potters Falls. The highest<br/>
I've run it is maybe 4.4' on the upper part and 5.5 on the lower part. We have run it as low as 3.4<br/>
more than once. </div>
</td>
</tr>
